'''Macleay's honeyeater''' ('''''Xanthotis macleayanus''''') is a [[honeyeater]] [[Endemism|endemic]] to [[Australia]]. Within Australia it has a limited distribution, occurring only in northern [[Queensland]] from [[Cooktown, Queensland|Cooktown]] to the southern end of the [[Paluma Range National Park|Paluma Range]].  Its natural [[habitat]]s are tropical dry [[forest]]s and tropical moist lowland forests.
